The paper deals with the problem of coalition structure generation, which is a fundamental problem in game theory and social choice theory. The problem involves partitioning a set of agents into disjoint coalitions, where the value of each coalition is determined by a valuation function. This problem is known to be NP-complete in general, and the paper provides new complexity results and algorithms for various classes of graphs and valuation functions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves graph algorithms and computational complexity analysis, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also proposes algorithms based on heuristic search and dynamic programming, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
